The article is a transcript of a press briefing given by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on September 16, 2009. The briefing covers various topics including the introduction of the Baucus healthcare bill, the ongoing evaluation of resources for Afghanistan, and discussions on race and healthcare reform. Gibbs emphasizes the importance of affordable healthcare and the need for a comprehensive strategy in Afghanistan. He also addresses concerns about the role of race in criticism of the President. Overall, the briefing provides updates on current issues and the administration's stance on various matters.